snippet.textDisplay: Rahat Fateh Ali Khan despite the talented legends of our generation is a big failure. Nusrat Fateh Ali Khan Saab and his party were the most special Qawwali Party in the world and since Rahat became his Janasheen, it's gotten down to this and other Salman Khan stuff in Bollywood. Besides, being an Indian myself, I don't think there's any singer in India-Pakistan who could make Sayonee their own. Salmaan might have gotten the best bassist, guitarists and drummers, or even the best vocalist Rahat, Sayonee is such an iconic song that can barely be taken away from it's original singer.
snippet.textOriginal: Rahat Fateh Ali Khan despite the talented legends of our generation is a big failure. Nusrat Fateh Ali Khan Saab and his party were the most special Qawwali Party in the world and since Rahat became his Janasheen, it's gotten down to this and other Salman Khan stuff in Bollywood. Besides, being an Indian myself, I don't think there's any singer in India-Pakistan who could make Sayonee their own. Salmaan might have gotten the best bassist, guitarists and drummers, or even the best vocalist Rahat, Sayonee is such an iconic song that can barely be taken away from it's original singer.
